WorldStage Newsonline– Niger Insurance Plc, a life and general insurance company in Nigeria underwriting all classes of insurance has notified the Nigerian Stock Exchange about the  unintended delay in the submission of its audited financial for the year ended 31st December 2019, saying it was awaiting approval from its primary regulator, National Insurance Commission (NAICOM) as same has been submitted. The notification signed by Tolg Nominees, Company Secretary said “The Board of Directors and Management of Niger Insurance Plc. hereby inform their esteemed Shareholders and other Stakeholders that Niger Insurance Plc’s Audited Financial Statements for the year ended 31st December, 2019 is currently awaiting approval from its primary regulator, National Insurance Commission (NAICOM) as same has been submitted. “The unintended delay in the submission resulted from the inadvertent delay in obtaining the required approval of its Accounts of which the Company has been closely following up. “While we are optimistic that the Audited Financial Statements will soon be submitted to the Exchange once approved by NAICOM, the Board and Management sincerely apologise for any inconvenience that this delay might have caused its Stakeholders.”